ra<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/dl.acm.org\/doi\/abs\/10.1145\/3492321.3519594\">Narwhal and Tusk: A DAG-based Mempool and Efficient BFT Consensus<\/a><br \/>\nGeorge Danezis, Lefteris Kokoris-Kogias, Alberto Sonnino, Alexander Spiegelman<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>Gilles Muller Best Artifact Award<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Nicholas Wanninger (Northwestern University), Kyle Hale (Illinois Institute of Technology), and Joshua Bowden (Illinois Institute of Technology) for their artifact &#8220;<a href=\"https:\/\/dl.acm.org\/doi\/10.1145\/3492321.3519553\">Isolating Functions at the Hardware Limit with Virtines<\/a>&#8220;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h5>Honorable Mentions<\/h5>\n<ul>\n<li>Jianbang Yang (Shanghai Jiao Tong University), Qiang Yin (Shanghai Jiao Tong University), Dahai Tang (Hunan university), Rong Chen (Shanghai Jiao Tong University), Xiaoniu Song (Shanghai Jiao Tong University), Wenyuan Yu (Alibaba Group), Lei Wang (Alibaba Group), and Jingren Zhou (Alibaba Group) for their artifact &#8220;<a href=\"https:\/\/dl.acm.org\/doi\/10.1145\/3492321.3519557\">GNNLab: A Factored System for Sample-based GNN Training over GPUs<\/a>&#8220;<\/li>\n<li>Kartal Kaan Bozdo\u011fan (Technical University of Munich), Shady Issa (Technical University of Munich),\u00a0 Dimitrios Stavrakakis (Technical University of Munich &amp; University of Edinburgh), Pramod Bhatotia (Technical University of Munich), for their artifact &#8220;<a href=\"https:\/\/dl.acm.org\/doi\/10.1145\/3492321.3519574\">SafePM: A Sanitizer for Persistent Memory<\/a>&#8220;<\/li>\n<li>J\u00f6rg Thalheim (TU Munich \/ University of Edinburgh), Harshavardhan Unnibhavi (TU Munich)<br \/>\nPramod Bhatotia (TU Munich), Peter Okelmann Redha Gouicem (TU Munich), for their artifact<br \/>\n&#8220;<a href=\"https:\/\/dl.acm.org\/doi\/10.1145\/3492321.3519589\">VMSH: Hypervisor-agnostic Guest Overlays for VMsb<\/a>&#8220;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>Distinguished Reviewer Artifact Award<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Alexios Voulimeneas (KU Leuven)<\/li>\n<\/ul>